        energy = rng.normal(loc=mean, scale=np.sqrt(variance), size=1) if 'energy' in percentiles else pulse_width * (rng.uniform(*percentiles[0])  # Energy calculation based on correlation with pulse_width or fixed range
        spot_size = rng.normal(loc=mean, scale=np.sqrt(variance), size=1) if 'spot_size' in percentiles else np.random.randint(min_val, max_val+1)  # Assuming a normal distribution for simplicity; otherwise apply similar logic
        intensity = rng.normal(loc=mean, scale=np.sqrt(variance), size=1) if 'intensity' in percentiles else spot_size * (rng.uniform(*percentiles[0])  # Intensity calculation based on correlation with spot_size or fixed range
        power = rng.normal(loc=mean, scale=np.sqrt(variance), size=1) if 'power' in percentiles else energy * (rng.uniform(*percentiles[0])  # Power calculation based on its own covariance with intensity or correlation with other features
